<DATELINE>YAROSLAVL, U.S.S.R. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Wearing a wide smile, the local <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> chief put his arm around an American visitor and steered him into his paneled office to watch the latest TV report on the <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> summit. `` May these sunny May days at the <LOCATION> Kremlin </LOCATION> mean that a new page has been turned in the history between our countries,'' <PERSON> Igor </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Tolstoukhov </PERSON> said at one point Tuesday. In <LOCATION> Volgograd </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Olga </PERSON> <PERSON> V. </PERSON> <PERSON> Sovelyova </PERSON> picked her way through a thick crowd when she heard there was an American nearby, removed her sunglasses and extended her hand. `` I want to congratulate you on the ratification of the medium-range missile treaty by your <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>,'' said the plump 41-year-old Russian woman. `` Things are looking up for relations between us.'' For a reporter on a 1,900-mile swing through the Russian heartland, the hopes inspired by the meeting between President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> and Soviet leader <PERSON> Mikhail </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gorbachev </PERSON> are immediately apparent because Soviets readily express them. `` I just wanted to say that we want to be friends with you,'' said a shy teen-aged girl in <LOCATION> Stavropol </LOCATION> who then left a bookstore on <PERSON> Karl </PERSON> <PERSON> Marx </PERSON> <PERSON> Prospekt </PERSON> that among other things sells posters condemning <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> militarism. If there is a <LOCATION> Peoria </LOCATION> in the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>, the <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> summit appears to be playing well there. That's the case even if the hopes it inspires are tempered by memories of past swings in superpower relations and the political fact that <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> will be out of office in January. For m