<HEAD>Hot Choreographer Does Pleasing Work for Ballet Theater</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: No PMs Planned</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By MARY CAMPBELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 `` Drink to Me Only with Thine Eyes,'' premiered by American Ballet Theater on Tuesday night at the <ORGANIZATION> Metropolitan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Opera </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION>, is a pleasing, light-hearted dance, the first choreographed for the company by <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Morris </PERSON>. <PERSON> Morris </PERSON>, who heads his own modern dance group, succeeds here by being interesting but not pushing cleverness too far and being inventive but not pushing that either. The mood of the dancing fit the mood of each of the 13 sections of music, from <PERSON> Virgil </PERSON> <PERSON> Thomson </PERSON>'s `` Etudes for Piano.'' Pianist <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Boriskin </PERSON> played a grand piano at the stage's rear center. <PERSON> Mikhail </PERSON> <PERSON> Baryshnikov </PERSON> danced but there is no `` star'' part. There was much coming and going. There were touches of humor, as when a dancer would enter at one side, dance straight across the stage and exit, or when dancers would enter, make a U-turn and return immediately to the wings. <PERSON> Morris </PERSON> sometimes repeated images, like having the women clasp their hands over their heads and lean back against their partner's arm He would walk around in a circle, partly carrying the ballerina's weight, with her pivoting on one toe. When <PERSON> Baryshnikov </PERSON> did solo figures, they were often turns, alternating clockwise and counterclockwise. He also skipped lightly, as well as doing regulation balletic jumps and turns in air. Three women danced a section where the center ballerina's legs were moving together while the other two ballerinas' legs were moving apart, all looking like an optical illusion. They concluded with a formal pose. <PERSON> Morris </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> Seattle </LOCATION> native, choreographed for the opera `` <PERSON> Nixon </PERSON> in <LOCATION> China </LOCATION>,'' as well as for the <ORGANIZATION> Seattle </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Opera </ORGANIZATION> presentations of `` Orpheus and Eurydice'' and `` Die Fledermaus.'' Next fall the <ORGANIZATION> Mark </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morris </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> will become the resident dance company of the <LOCATION> Brussels </LOCATION> theater, which formerly housed <PERSON> Maurice </PERSON> <PERSON> Bejart </PERSON>'s Ballet of the 20th Century. Also on Tuesday's program at the Met were <PERSON> Baryshnikov </PERSON>'s staging of `` Grand Pas Classique'' from `` Raymonda'' and the lavish production of <PERSON> Leonide </PERSON> <PERSON> Massine </PERSON>'s `` Gaite Parisienne,'' which is new this season.
