<HEAD>Dollar And Stocks Both Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The dollar finished higher Wednesday in trading against the Japanese yen in <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>, while stock prices posted a strong gain. The dollar closed at 125.35 yen, up 0.55 yen from Tuesday's finish It opened the day at 125.23 yen and ranged between 125.10 and 125.37 yen. On the <ORGANIZATION> Tokyo </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Nikkei </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Average </ORGANIZATION> of 225 selected issues, a 193.60-point winner Tuesday, added another 287.21 points, or 1.04 percent, to close the day's trading at 27,703.91. `` The thrust of the dollar's upward momentum is not so strong,'' said a senior dealer at a major commercial bank who spoke on condition of anonymity. `` Share prices rallied almost across the board, helped by the notion among many market participants that rising <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> interest rates have peaked out,'' said <PERSON> Seiichiro </PERSON> <PERSON> Kita </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Daiwa </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION>, a major Japanese brokerage. <PERSON> Kita </PERSON> and other securities company officials said the <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> stock market was also encouraged by a 74.68-point surge in the Dow Jones industrial average on Wall Street overnight.
