<HEAD>Salvadoran President Undergoes Tests In United States Military
Hospital</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PAUL RECER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Salvadoran President <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Napolean </PERSON> <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON>, admitted to <ORGANIZATION> Walter </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reed </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> for treatment of what he called a bleeding ulcer `` of a malignant nature,'' began tests today to determine if his condition could be cancer. <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON>, 62, was taken to <PERSON> Walter </PERSON> <PERSON> Reed </PERSON> after arriving Tuesday night at <ORGANIZATION> Andrews </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Base </ORGANIZATION> near <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Walter </PERSON> <PERSON> Reed </PERSON> spokesman <PERSON> Pete </PERSON> <PERSON> Esker </PERSON> said today that <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> `` rested comfortably last night and began medical evaluation and tests this morning. `` He is in good spirits and his condition is stable,'' <PERSON> Esker </PERSON> said in a short statement. `` It is not appropriate to comment further until all his tests are completed.'' <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON>'s illness has been described by those around him as both an `` ulcer'' and as `` a tumor.'' The Salvadoran president himself said it was an ulcer of `` a malignant nature.'' A physician who is an expert on stomach diseases, but who is not associated with <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON>'s care, said that it often is difficult to determine if an illness is the result of an ulcer or is caused by a stomach cancer. `` It is not at all uncommon for there to be confusion,'' said Dr. <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Hamilton </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cancer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION>. `` When you look at the two things, they may be very similar.'' Extensive tests or even surgery may be required to