<HEAD>City Covers Up Law's Loophole</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents</NOTE>
<DATELINE>EL PASO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Tape, sheer fabric and grease are no longer enough between topless dancers and their audience. City Council has amended a pornography ordinance that previously specified what body parts had to be covered but not that the covering had to be opaque. The council changed that on Tuesday. Some women `` were covering their breasts with Vaseline or grease, because the ordinance did not say what type of covering was needed,'' said <PERSON> Brenda </PERSON> <PERSON> Nichols </PERSON>, assistant city attorney. There also were reports that women used see-through fabric or clear tape to skirt the ordinance. <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> is trying to stamp out adult businesses, said <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Gibson </PERSON>, a lawyer who represents some of the businesses. `` If you comply with the first ordinance they pass, they change it to make sure no one can comply,'' he said. The amendment takes effect immediately, and anyone violating it is subject to arrest. Strip shows are allowed by law, but the adult entertainment business has to be at least 1,000 feet from homes, schools, churches, parks or other adult establishments.
</TEXT>
