TION>'s maintenance inspection system. <ORGANIZATION> Aloha </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> officials have said repeatedly that they followed all required inspections on the <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION> 737 that broke apart in flight. `` It obviously was n't sufficient,'' said <PERSON> Enders </PERSON>, the aviation consultant. `` The -LRB- <LOCATION> Aloha </LOCATION> -RRB- inspections were not enough to give the early warning signs.''
