<HEAD>OPEC Meeting Postponed, Report Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries has postponed its ministerial conference in <LOCATION> Vienna </LOCATION> next week to avoid clashing with an Arab leaders' meeting in <LOCATION> Algiers </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> reported in Thursday editions. The business daily quoted unidentified sources as saying that because of the Arab summit, the <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> meeting scheduled to begin on Wednesday will be postponed to either June 10 or June 11.
